After simplification, we have `‖1 / i‖ ^ 2`. In `ℝ`, the norm is the absolute value.

So, we need to show `|1 / i| ^ 2 < ∞`.

If `i = 0`, then `1 / i = 1 / 0 = 0` in Lean. So `‖0‖ ^ 2 = |0| ^ 2 = 0 ^ 2 = 0 < ∞`.

If `i > 0`, then `1 / i` is a positive real number. `‖1 / i‖ = |1 / i| = 1 / i`. So we need to show `(1 / i) ^ 2 < ∞`. The sum `∑ (1 / i) ^ 2` converges, so each term is finite. Therefore, `(1 / i) ^ 2 < ∞`.

So the proof is to show that `∑ (1 / i) ^ 2` converges.

